The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      IN THE CITY
                  
	The tournament committee of the Indian Football Association (IFA) will meet on Friday to discuss the match commissioner and referees report on the issue of Chirag players manhandling referee Minangshu Bhattacharjee during the CFL Premier Division title decider on Tuesday. Meanwhile, Mohun Bagan secretary Anjan Mitra wrote a letter to IFA secretary Utpal Ganguli demanding strong action against the players who roughed up the referee.          
	ITF official Joy Mukherjee has been nominated as the tournament referee for an Asian U-14 event in Ahmedabad from May 31.          
	Standard Chartered beat Apeejay Surendra 3-0 in a five-a-side invitational tournament for The Telegraph Cup 2010 being presented by McDowells No.1 at the CC amp;FC ground.      
	Results: Samsara Shipping 2 Indian Chamber of Commerce 0; Panchwati Hotel Resorts 3 Wesman 0; The Telegraph 0 ITC B 3; Bighnesh Capital 1 TCS A 4; Selvel Blue 4 IMRB 0                
	 South Point High School A beat St Josephs Convent B in the senior boys fours category of the BRC Students Rowing Championship at the Rabindra Sarovar on Wednesday. In the senior girls fours, Birla High got the better of St Thomas A.                
	Football: I-League: East Bengal vs Viva Kerala (Howrah Stadium, 3:30 pm)      
